<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/964615378ff128c4706951378f3ffb23.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 3 and A = 60 degrees. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place.  Give angles in <em>degrees</em>
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>1.7</li><li>3.5</li><li>30.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p>For the length of the other leg,</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\tan{{\left({60}\right)}}}=\frac{{3}}{{b}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}=\frac{{3}}{{\tan{{\left({60}\right)}}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}\approx{1.7320508075689}\approx{1.7}</m>.</p>
<p>For the third side</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={3}^{{2}}+{1.7320508075689}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={9}+{3}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={12}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{12}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{3.4641016151378}\approx{3.5}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{60}^{\circ}\approx{30}^{\circ}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

